title: Great
text: We over ordered here as the pizzas are big and a reasonable price. Had 2 large pizzas and 4 toppings and they were really good. Delivery guy was also quick.

title: Lovely
text: Went here for a round of golf and the day after to use the driving range. Beautiful world class course at an affordable price. Also has a nice restaurant with some amazing pies.
placeLocation: King Abdullah Economic City, Saudi Arabia

title: Alright
text: Enjoyed my trip here because I got new trainers (fast ones). Got some shops and a few food choices . Only recycling opportunity I've seen in Saudi on the car park.

title: Nice
text: Saw this on the tour but wasn't allowed to see the other side. Looks nice and a good start to the tour around Hegra.

title: Very nice
text: These rocks are the things that make you want to visit Al Ula. Beautiful place and I think it will offer more in time.

title: Alright
text: Had food here last night and it was all perfectly nice. Service was a little awkward but of a higher standard than normal. Some dishes were overpriced such as the camel meatballs. Food was cooked well with nothing overpowering.

title: Basic
text: Some basic info a train to take pictures of and some restored buildings. Stopped at a few places similar on the drive from Yanbu to Al Ula.

title: Average
text: I think this is your only choice of pizza in Al Ula. Not great but perfectly edible. Service is quick and they have lots of choice.

title: Excellent
text: Can only go on booked tours now. They are quick and leave from the winter park. Winter park has a few coffee shops and a burger king. Really nice park if you want to spend a bit of time having a picnic before or after the tour. The tour is efficient and you are given water and dates as you go. Might want to have a bit of a read before you go if you want lots of information but the guides can give you the general idea. If you have a small child I wouldn't take a pushchair just carry.

title: Old town road
text: Had a nice tour and a walk around the old town at night. Not fully finished but you can get the idea. Tour lasts about an hour and you are given very basic information, some water and dates. It's a bit annoying that you have to drive to the winter park to get a bus that will take you there. Has some restaurant s and shops that are nice to visit at night. Not a good idea to take a stroller.

title: Ok
text: It's your normal steakhouse you will find in the rest of Saudi. Nice outdoor area out front. Free child's meal on a Monday.
placeLocation: King Abdullah Economic City, Saudi Arabia

title: Good
text: Had some food here and ate it in the car because we didn't want to leave our sleeping baby. I had a buffalo sandwich and the wife had a rabbit. Was tasty even tho I had to eat it in silence. Guy at the counter was polite.

title: Worth a look
text: We went here just before shutting and maybe should have gone earlier. Lovely setting and what we had from the menu was good but maybe a little on the expensive side. However we did get a great view and a 5 piece band playing so that was reflected in the price.

title: Lovely
text: Well worth a visit. We drove their for sunset and found a nice spot in the desert. Lots of little trails there so go a little before if you have the time.

title: Average
text: If your expecting your typical Radisson blu then you are going to be disappointed. It's a UK 3 star but a low quality one or a USA 2 star. Service is fine and rooms are clean for the night with an average breakfast. Handy place to stop when driving from Jeddah to Al Ula. Paid extra for business floor and this is a con as the lounge is not open and you get nothing extra don't be tempted.

title: Not good
text: Some of the worst food I've ever had. Only had nachos and the ones I received were awful. They used one little cube of tomato as salsa and covered the greasy tacos in fake cheese. Service was also poor. I didn't even eat them.

title: Standard
text: Not the best pizza but the normal Domino standard. Messed up and got 2 pizzas with white sauce. Was recommended the kicking chicken and it was alright. Ross didn't like the cinnamon twists said they were dry.

title: Solid
text: Really quick and food is tasty. You can also get big portions to eat at home. I usually get a burrito

title: Still good
text: Had a burger and fries from here and it was as good as ever. Burgers are well good but get at least 2 patties on it.

title: Same same
text: Same coffee as usual but really lovely staff and always welcome. Liza should get promoted just for being sound.

title: Good burger
text: This is a really nice burger for the price. Small but really tasty and tastes similar to shake shack. Chicken wings are tiny but tasty. Would order from here again.

title: Center
text: Lots of tall buildings and looks nice at night if you want to take some pictures. Decent paths if you want to walk around.

title: Worth a look
text: Worth a look when in Manama old ruins and a nice place to walk around with sea views. Hot in the afternoon

title: Worth a look
text: Had a look around here this afternoon and enjoyed the walk. Lots of walls still intact and good views of the new city.

title: Not good
text: I like wagamama and usually enjoy the food. This was horrid what I had today and didn't taste like any wagamama I've ever had. The gyoza was overdrives and really greasy with a horrid sauce. The pad Thai was revolting and had no fresh flavours and was oily. Fire cracker chicken mainly tasted of soy sauce. Wasn't pleased at all.

title: Same as always
text: Got some takeaway from Talabat and it was delivered hot and quickly. We like the buffalo tacos and they were good.

title: Good mall
text: Overall a good mall with cinema and a good range of shops. Wish it had a supermarket in it as I was staying nearby and it would have been convenient.

title: Handy
text:
The hotel is very close to terminal 5 and only a ten minute walk away. Everything is shut at the hotel at the minute so can't use the facilities.

I couldn't give it more than 3 stars as we arrived went to our room stayed there and left. Was meant to get a few drinks as I was Expedia gold but this was never offered.

I also thought the room service prices were ridiculous as they have a captive audience.

title: Good
text: You get a nice hot meal here at a fair price. Screens to watch sport and the service is always nice.

title: Massive
text: A frame can be seen from miles around. Got lots of information underneath and must have been a sight to see back in the day.

title: Lovely
text: Love going here for walks around the woods. Good swing park for the kids and usually not busy and quiet. Get some food at boswell coach house afterwards.

title: War memorial
text: Went here a few days ago while out for a walk. We'll kept war memorial with very little information around it. If you like lurking around Old cemeteries try the one on the barrhill.

title: Greggs
text: Got a steak bake the other day. Forgot how good they were. Sausage rolls are good but only gets 4 stars because the flakey pastry gets everywhere.

title: Spicy
text: Got some takeaway from here. The food was good and had a nice kick. Food was reasonably authentic and I would eat here again.

title: Bk
text: Had a burger King after not eating fast food for a while. I always regret eating burger King and this was no different.

title: Bridge
text: Handy bridge that saves you swimming or going to another bridge. Some people climb up on it. Worth a look when walking down the Clyde.

title: Needle
text: Center piece of the park where protests meet and people stop for a picnic on a good day. First monument built in honour of Lord Nelson.

title: Love it
text: This is one of my favourite places in Glasgow. If you want to go a run have a picnic or do some sightseeing this place is ideal. Home to the the world's tallest terracotta fountain and the first monument to Nelson after his famous Battle.

title: Average
text: It's a good kebab with decent ingredients. The sides are also pretty nice. The reason it's average is the wait times are long for a fast food place. Timings on deliveroo were continually put back and I waited over an hour and a half and its not that far from me. Price is also expensive for what you get.

title: Fave
text: I think this is one of the best lounges to chill in T5. Always quiet food is alright but always enough and good views.

title: Didn't like it
text: Service was robotic and slow. I asked for an espresso and she replied you want an expresso. This annoyed me. I drank my espresso it was alright but not great.

title: Airport food
text: I think it's important to remember this is airport food. I like how this restaraunt makes you feel like your not in the airport. Has lots of charging station for devices. I had a burger and it was pretty good but not the best I've ever had. The chocolate tart for desert was excellent.

title: Good
text: The burgers here are good and the they are always fresh. Just a little expensive when there are loads of burger places in Jeddah.

title: Nice
text: Good food here and really friendly service. The food is similar to local hotels but the dining room is nice and handy for parking. Would go back again as it is a good option for Cumnock if you are in the area.

title: Paesano
text: We really like Paesano in the city center and this one is the same menu. Cool building and delicious pizza.

title: Good place
text: For the price and the portions and the quality of food this place is good. Meat is cooked well and burgers are tasty. Drinks are very reasonable. There is an English menu and service is adequate. Tom got his burger served the way he wanted and we usually have problems with this.

title: Alright
text: The burger was really good and was reasonably priced. Onion rings were very tasty and had a good crunch but the fries were cheap frozen ones. Milkshake was also poor and had a cheap vanilla taste to it like they have used vanilla custard instead of ice cream.

title: Good food
text: The food here is good and I would recommend going. Good price and the meat is very good. Service is a little slow but wouldn't stop me going back.

title: Ok
text: This was nice Indian food but like many people have said it is completely over priced. 36sar for rice is extreme.

title: Good
text: Had a vegan breakfast and it was really tasty and well done. If they had gave another slice of toast it would have got 5. Coffee was also good.

title: 1 night
text: Stayed here 1 night with friends. Room was fine nothing fancy but was clean and plenty of space. Room was a little cold and could have been doing with a little more heat but not too bad. Shower was hot. Good location close to lots of stuff. For the price I would stay here again.

title: Excellent
text: Saw this place online and heard good things about it and it didn't dissapoint. Service was really friendly and food and coffee were really good.

title: Nice
text: Nice place for lunch with some good choices. Dessert was very average but mains were good. Service was very friendly.

title: Shops
text: It's a bunch of shops similar to what you would find on most high streets. Or you can go to Ralph Lauren get some stuff on a credit card and pretend you have more money than you actually do.

title: Good food
text: Good solid food at a reasonable price. Decor is a little bit quirky and service is friendly. Soup was very hot.

title: Slow
text: Had to wait a while for a coffee here and it was just an espresso. Waited a while for the toilet and when I did finally get in they were disgusting.

title: Nice
text: A nice friendly pub where we popped in for a few drinks. Some good offers and friendly service. Football was also shown.

title: Brilliant
text: The building is amazing as soon as you enter and the decorations for Christmas help. Both pastas we had were delicious and service was fast and friendly the same as paesano. A few wine options and glad punk ipa is on the menu. Will definetly be going back to try other pastas on the menu.

title: Value
text: Not the best chippy I have ever been too but cheap and made to order. Would go back if I was in Irvine but wouldn't go out of my way for it.
